
<seller>NEWMONT MINING CORP</seller> REDUCES STAKE IN <acqabr>PEABODY</acqabr>
    NEW YORK, APril 1 - <seller>Newmont Mining Corp</seller> said it <status>completed</status>
the previously announced reduction of its share in {<acquired>Peabody
Holding Co Inc</acquired>} to 49.97 pct from 61.47 pct.
    <sellerabr>Newmont</sellerabr> realized <dlramt>116.8 mln dlrs</dlramt> in the transaction.
    For 1986, <sellerabr>Newmont</sellerabr> reported net income of 74.2 mln dlrs.
<acqabr>Peabody</acqabr>, the largest <acqbus>coal</acqbus> producer in the U.S., had net income
of 100.8 mln dlrs on sales of 1.4 billion dlrs in 1986.
    <sellerabr>Newmont</sellerabr> doubled its ownership in <acqabr>Peabody</acqabr> in January by
purchasing 30.74 pct interest held by the Williams Cos for 320
mln dlrs.
    The reduction resulted from completion of an earlier
announced agreement by <acqabr>Peabody</acqabr> to sell a 15.01 pct interest in
the company to Eastern Gas and Fuel Associates in exchange for
